FBIS4-52018 "dreas087_d_94003" FBIS-EAS-94-087 Daily Report 4 May 1994 South Korea Convicted Japanese Journalist Deported Convicted Japanese Journalist Deported SK0405124194 Seoul YONHAP in English 1133 GMT 4 May 94 SK0405124194 Seoul YONHAP English BFN [Text] Seoul, May 4 (YONHAP) -- The Japanese Fuji-TV Seoul bureau chief, who has been sentenced to a suspended prison term for violating the military secret protection law, was deported from Korea on last April 28, a Justice Ministry official said Wednesday. The Japanese journalist, Masatoshi Sinohara, has drawn two years in prison with a stay of execution for three years. The appellate court verdict was confirmed as he did not appeal. "Under the immigration law, those foreigners sentenced to prison terms are supposed to be deported. We have also banned him from visiting Korea for the next five years," the Ministry official said.
